message.content:
I need to identify costs incurred to secure customer orders and deliver goods and services.

Looking at the income statement, these types of costs would typically be found in:
1. Selling Expenses - These are costs related to marketing, sales, and delivering products to customers
2. Cost of Goods Sold - These represent direct costs of producing goods or services

In this income statement, the "Selling Expenses" line item specifically captures the costs incurred to secure customer orders and deliver goods/services to customers. The amount listed is 1,325,774.90.
